    {
      "id": "a0917da947389edb2e290ae3e1eefadb3cabc83a",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2013-03-08 07:00:47.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\nThe overall code looks good, but I think there is a defect in zfs_set_prop_int(). It is passed a void pointer, which is typecast to an unsigned long, but previously this was passed a __u32 field. On a 65-bit system this would turn the pointer to a 32-but value to a 64-bit value possibly containing garbage. Also, the use of unsigned long doesn't jibe with the function name.\n\nI _think_ the 32-bit value is correct, and just the typecast and printf() format need to be change.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "16aabff5d44e9a6b181cfbe209c3eb96c0e24a2d",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 124,
        "name": "Prakash Surya",
        "email": "lists@prakashsurya.com",
        "username": "prakash"
      },
      "date": "2013-03-08 07:33:40.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nThanks for the quick review, Andreas. I was confused about that when I was looking at the previous iteration, which casted the param to a unsigned long. If that looks wrong to you too, I'll change it to a __u32 which is what the passed in parameter should be.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "cfc4a2061dd345875affa3686a9a89b3fc82f7ec",
      "author": {
